sorcer.service

Interface Signature

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Arg, java.lang.Comparable, Dependency, EvaluationComponent, Identifiable, Request, java.io.Serializable, Service, SupportComponent
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EvaluationSignature, ModelSignature, NetletSignature, NetSignature, ObjectSignature, ServiceSignature

    public interface Signature
extends Request, java.lang.Comparable, Dependency, Identifiable, Arg, EvaluationComponent, SupportComponent, java.io.Serializable
    A service Signature is an indirect behavioral feature of Exertions that declares a service that can be performed by instances of Services. It contains a service fiType and a selector of operation of that service fiType (interface). Its implicit parameter and return value is a service Context. Thus, the explicit signature of service-oriented operations is defined by the same Context fiType for any exertion parameter and return value . A signature may include a collection of optional attributes describing a preferred Service with a given service fiType. Also a signature can carry own implementation when its fiType is implemented with the provided codebase.

    In other words, a service signature is a specification of a service that can be requested dynamically at the boundary of a service provider. Operations include modifying a service Context or disclosing information about the service context.
